textAfterTable: 2011-12 Individual Stats 2011-12: Yohn played in all 27 games for the Cobra women, starting 14 games in 2011-12. She averaged 6.8 points per game and shot 33.3 percent from 3-point range. She also averaged 2.4 rebounds per game. Hailey scored a season high 15 points twice, the first time against Bellarmine (11/26) and the second against Belmont Abbey (2/11). She was also 5-for-6 from three-point land against Belmont Abbey. High School: The all-time leader in three-point shots made for Northern HS, Yohn averaged 10 PPG and was a member of the 2010 Glaxo Invitational Tournament championship team.  She was also named All-Conference twice, All-Region and was a N.C. State 4A all-tournament team selection. Personal: Daughter of Jeanne and Jeff Yohn...she has one sister, Mandi. Recent Games Feb 17 at Catawba L, 47-44 Feb 19 Wingate L, 54-52 Feb 22 Anderson (S.C.)
